  "texts": [
    "Recent research by Salih and Al-Ani (2024) focused on designing an intelligent electronic nose (E-nose) for odor detection, utilizing the Smell Inspector developer kit equipped with multiple gas sensors and environmental monitoring features.",
    "The study demonstrated the capability of the E-nose to create digital fragrance fingerprints and employ machine learning techniques, including K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN), for odor recognition.",
    "The results showed a 78% accuracy in identifying various odors, such as clean air, onion, and gasoline, highlighting the potential of enhanced E-nose technology for realtime smell detection applications.",
    "AI's influence extends significantly into healthcare, where olfactory systems are increasingly employed for early disease diagnosis.",
    "Electronic noses utilizing deep learning algorithms have shown promise in detecting volatile organic compounds (VOCs) in human breath, allowing for the identification of diseases such as lung cancer and Parkinson's disease."
